title: Trump's brutal threat to ‘traitors’ who told the military to ‘disobey’ orders
description: US President Donald Trump has unleashed on “traitors” who told the military to “disobey” his orders.  In a statement on Truth Social, Trump sent a warning to Democrats in response to a recent video.  The video Trump was referring to was a social media post with Democrat Senators and Representatives calling for the army to ignore “illegal” orders.  In his post, Trump called on those involved in the video to be “in jail right now”, labelling it as “sedation at the highest level”.  Democrat Senator Elissa Slotkin on ABC was pressed on the video implying President Trump is “having illegal orders”.

title: Jacinta Allan bats away question on James Packer calling Dan Andrews ‘human filth’
description: Victorian Premier Jacinta Allan has declined to comment on billionaire James Packer calling former Victorian premier Dan Andrews ‘human filth’.  “I’m focused on what Victorians expect their government and their premier to be focused on,” Ms Allen said.  “And that includes getting the metro tunnel ready to be open in six days time.”

title: Bill Maher roasts Jimmy Kimmel’s wife after Trump-voting family refused to ‘obey’ her ‘ultimatum’
description: Comedian Bill Maher has roasted Jimmy Kimmel’s wife after she gave her Trump-voting family an “ultimatum” before the election.  The ‘Real Time’ host reacted to Molly McNearney’s comments during an appearance on the ‘We Can Do Hard Things’ podcast on November 6.  During the podcast, McNearney revealed that before the election, she reached out to conservative family members in a late effort to sway their vote.  Maher spoke about people cutting off family members over politics before addressing McNearney’s comments directly.  The comedian slammed McNearney for cutting ties with her Trump-supporting family because they did not “obey” her orders not to vote for him.

title: ‘Disgraceful’: Labor has ‘gone silent’ on $96 million BOM website redesign
description: Nationals Leader David Littleproud claims there is a “cultural deficiency” at the Bureau of Meteorology following a $96 million website redesign.  “I don’t know where Murray Watt is, he’s gone silent on this, he is the minister responsible,” Mr Littleproud told Sky News Australia.  “This is a disgrace for the Bureau of Meteorology; they’ve had a litany of errors.”

title: ‘We’ve got to sell our plan’: The Coalition defends its  energy plan amid slumping polls
description: Shadow Energy and Emissions Reduction Minister Dan Tehan says the Coalition needs to sell its energy plan after being questioned on slumping polls.  “We’re going to put energy affordability as the number one priority when it comes to the national electricity market,” Mr Tehan told Sky News Australia.  “If we don’t step on the gas, then our whole energy system is going to be incredibly vulnerable.”

title: ‘There’s a cheaper way’: Littleproud sends ‘strong signals’ to Labor’s $9 trillion energy plan
description: Nationals leader David Littleproud claims Prime Minister Anthony Albanese is “out of touch” with the “pain and hurt” of Labor’s net zero plan on the Australian people.  “This government wants to commit Australia to reducing its emissions by 4.8 per cent every year between now and 2035,” Mr Littleproud told Sky News Australia.   “There’s a cheaper, better, fairer way.”

title: 'Human filth': James Packer verbally attacks Dan Andrews
description: Billionaire businessman James Packer has slammed former Victorian premier Daniel Andrews on a podcast, saying Andrews had “betrayed” him.  Mr Packer claims Mr Andrews introduced a surprise tax, which derailed a Crown Resorts deal.  “I couldn’t speak more lowly of Daniel Andrews. I think he’s human filth,” Mr Packer said.

title: Labor abandons defence honours reform after receiving mass backlash
description: Labor has abandoned its proposed overhaul of the defence honours system.  Mass backlash from veterans has forced a change of course, with the government now facing calls to apologise.  This comes as the Albanese Labor government was attempting to limit the awarding of retrospective medals and the review of that process.   Retired lieutenant colonel George Hulse described the reform as a “regressive, repressive, oppressive” piece of legislation.

title: Calls for ‘united’ front against Russia as Trump condemns Europe for buying Russian oil
description: Ukraine's Ambassador to Australia Vasyl Myroshnychenko discusses ongoing peace talks taking place in Geneva.   “Our position is the following: to force Russia into peace, we need to be united, and we need to exert that pressure jointly, which includes imposing more sanctions,” Mr Myroshnychenko told Sky News Australia.   “That means more sanctions on the Russian companies and the Russian leaders and entities.  “This is how we can force Russia into peace.”

title: Labor’s first home buyer scheme will have ‘some impact’ on house price increases
description: REA Group Senior Economist Angus Moore says Labor’s first home buyer deposit scheme should have a moderate impact on the demand for properties in affordable parts of the market, where first home buyers are typically active.  “We wouldn’t expect this to translate immediately into home prices, it takes a little while,” Mr Moore told Sky News Australia.   “These changes will clearly bring some first home buyer demand forward, allowing some first home buyers to buy a bit sooner.  “That will have some impact on home prices.”   Sponsored by realestate.com.au

title: ‘Low IQ’ Jasmine Crockett heavily roasted for unhinged remarks
description: Democrat Representative Jasmine Crockett’s latest unhinged remarks have sparked a mass roast online.  Crockett, who has repeatedly been called “low-IQ” by US President Donald Trump, recently discussed immigration.  The Democrat recently spoke to an audience where she said illegal immigration was “good fiscal policy”.  Crockett also stated that the Supreme Court was “trash” and called for its expansion and reform.  Representative Crockett has also reacted to US Representative Marjorie Taylor Greene announcing she will be resigning in the new year.

title: Italian PM Giorgia Meloni calls for the end to Russia's ‘unjustified’ war
description: Italian Prime Minister Giorgia Meloni has called out Russia's unjust war in Ukraine.  Meloni's comments came during the G20 summit in Johannesburg, South Africa.  The Italian Prime Minister goes on to say her country is ready to work with the US and Europe to reach a just peace.  Meloni's comments as US Secretary of State Marco Rubio is in Geneva, Switzerland for ongoing peace talks.

title: Firefighter dies while battling blaze in South Australia
description: A firefighter has died while battling a blaze on South Australia's Eyre Peninsula.  Firefighter Peter Curtis was working as part of a crew of 12 personnel on a fire that started in a conservation park on Saturday.  A search was launched after firefighters discovered there was an unaccounted member at the fireground.  The firefighter was later found at the site but was unable to be revived.

title: Trump to take on Somali Gangs in Minnesota with savage warning to Tim Walz
description: US President Donald Trump has announced a move to end temporary protected status for Somalis in Minnesota.  In a savage post to Truth Social, Trump said Minnesota under Governor Tim Walz had become a "hub" of "fraudulent money laundering activity".  "I am, as President of the United States, hereby terminating, effective immediately, the Temporary Protected Status (TPS Program) for Somalis in Minnesota," Trump posted.  "Somali gangs are terrorising the people of that great State, and BILLIONS of Dollars are missing. Send them back to where they came from. It's OVER! President DJT".  In response, Walz slammed President Trump, saying he was trying to "change the subject".

title: Labor MP accuses Nationals backbench of 'driving' Coalition policy development
description: Assistant Minister to the Prime Minister Patrick Gorman accuses the Nationals backbench of driving the entirety of Coalition policy development.  “You’d have to be a very good spin doctor for the Liberal Party to say that Barnaby Joyce’s bill from the backbench is somehow good for their leader, Sussan Ley,” Mr Gorman told Sky News Australia.  “Clearly, it is the backbench of the National Party that is driving the entirety of Coalition policy development.”
